## Why This Is Asked
This question tests end-to-end lifecycle management, macro-driven multi-tenant infrastructure, governance capabilities, and auditability. It evaluates proficiency in dynamic object creation, safe removal procedures, data lag handling, and implementing isolation checks.

## Key Concepts
- dbt macros and dynamic SQL generation
- Snowflake object lifecycle management (schemas, grants, drops)
- Tenant lifecycle governance (onboarding/offboarding)
- Row-level security policies and audit trails
- CI validation for per-tenant artifacts and isolation enforcement

## Code Example
```sql
{% macro create_tenant_schema(tenant) %}
  EXECUTE IMMEDIATE 'CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS analytics_' ~ tenant;
  {% set grant_stmt %}
    GRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA analytics_{{ tenant }} TO ROLE analytics_user;
    GRANT SELECT ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA analytics_{{ tenant }} TO ROLE analytics_user;
  {% endset %}
  {% do run_query(grant_stmt) %}
{% endmacro %}
```

## Implementation Considerations
- Schema-drift detection using information_schema comparisons
- 1-day data lag handling with window functions and watermark checks
- Cross-tenant isolation tests using query result validation
- CI pipeline steps to validate tenant status alignment with object existence
- Comprehensive audit logging for all schema changes

## Why This Is Asked

Tests ability to design registry-driven per-tenant masking, consistent lineage, and CI across tenants, while handling late data and schema drift.

## Key Concepts

- Macro-based per-tenant masking
- Dynamic per-tenant schemas from a registry
- Schema drift guards and late data handling
- Global lineage tracking and cross-tenant isolation in CI

## Code Example

```javascript
// simplified macro skeleton
{% macro mask_for_tenant(field, tenant) -%}
  {% if tenant in var('full_access_tenants') -%}
    {{ field }}
  {% else -%}
    sha256({{ field }})
  {% endif -%}
{%- endmacro %}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you test masking correctness across tenants in CI?
- How would you handle a tenant revocation of access mid-cycle?

