## Why This Is Asked

Tests the ability to design an adaptive per-tenant pipeline, leveraging dbt macros to route between data paths, while keeping data consistent and isolated. It also probes how velocity-based decisions, late data, and lineage are codified in CI and tests.

## Key Concepts

- Per-tenant velocity in analytics_{{tenant}}.config
- Adaptive path selection: MERGE upsert vs FULL_REFRESH
- Idempotence with last_hash for dedup
- Late data handling (2-day window)
- Tests: not_null on (tenant_id, day, metric_id); unique constraint on (tenant_id, day, metric_id)
- Cross-tenant isolation via per-tenant schemas and RLS-like controls
- Global lineage tracking across adaptive paths

## Code Example

```sql
-- dbt macro sketch: select path per tenant
{% macro tenant_path(tenant) %}
  {% set velocity = (var('tenant_' ~ tenant ~ '_velocity') | default(0)) | int %}
  {% if velocity > 10000 %}
    {{ return('MERGE') }}
  {% else %}
    {{ return('FULL_REFRESH') }}
  {% endif %}
{% endmacro %}
```

