## Why This Question Is Asked
This question evaluates a candidate's ability to design tenant-scoped anomaly detection using incremental dbt models, custom macros, and robust CI gates in a multi-tenant Snowflake environment.

## Key Concepts
- Incremental dbt modeling scoped per tenant
- Per-tenant statistical summaries (sigma computation)
- CI gates for production safety
- Automated scheduling with Snowflake TASKS

## Code Example
```javascript
// macros/analytics_base.sql
{% macro compute_sigma(tenant) %}
  {% set stats_table = 'analytics_base.tenant_stats' %}
  SELECT mean, stddev(value) AS sigma
  FROM {{ ref('tenant_events') }}
  WHERE tenant = '{{ tenant }}'
  GROUP BY tenant, event_type
{% endmacro %}

// models/analytics_{{tenant}}/daily_anomalies.sql
{{ config(materialized='incremental', unique_key='date') }}

WITH sigma AS (
  SELECT * FROM {{ analytics_base.compute_sigma(var('tenant')) }}
),
anomalies AS (
  SELECT
    e.tenant,
    DATE(e.event_ts) AS date,
    e.event_type,
    e.value,
    (e.value - s.mean) / NULLIF(s.sigma, 0) AS z_score,
    CASE WHEN ABS((e.value - s.mean) / NULLIF(s.sigma, 0)) > 3 THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE END AS is_anomaly
  FROM {{ ref('staging.tenant_events') }} e
  JOIN sigma s ON e.event_type = s.event_type AND e.tenant = s.tenant
  {% if is_incremental() %}
  WHERE DATE(e.event_ts) > (SELECT MAX(date) FROM {{ this }})
  {% endif %}
)
SELECT * FROM anomalies
```

## Why This Matters
This interview question tests your understanding of macro correctness, multi-tenant schema templating, and CI/CD integration for data quality enforcement.

## Key Concepts
- dbt macros and singular/generic tests
- Per-tenant schemas using `analytics_{{tenant}}` naming convention
- CI gating: blocking deploys when any tenant's test reports NULL violations

## Code Example
```sql
-- analytics_base/macros/not_null_guard.sql
{% macro not_null_guard(tenant, model, col) %}
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM analytics_{{ tenant }}.{{ model }} WHERE {{ col }} IS NULL) = 0
{% endmacro %}
```

```sql
-- tests/generic/not_null_guard.sql
{% test not_null_guard(model, col) %}
  {% if execute %}
    {% set result = run_query(not_null_guard(this.name, model, col)) %}
    {% if result.rows[0][0] | int != 0 %}
      {% do exceptions.raise_compile_error(
        "Failed: " ~ model ~ "." ~ col ~ " contains NULL values"
      ) %}
    {% endif %}
  {% endif %}
{% endtest %}
```

The test verifies zero NULL values exist in the target column across all tenant-specific models.

## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design per-tenant masking, macro-driven schema generation, and lineage tracking in dbt, while enforcing isolation and late data.

## Key Concepts
- Macro-driven per-tenant schemas
- Policy-based PII masking (redact, hash, partial)
- Global lineage table and dependency tracking
- Late-arrival handling and tenant isolation CI

## Code Example

```sql
-- macro: mask_pii
{% macro mask_pii(policy, field) -%}
  {% if policy == 'redact' -%}
    NULL
  {% elif policy == 'hash' -%}
    SHA2(CONCAT(COALESCE('{{tenant_id}}', 'global'), {{field}}), 256)
  {% else -%}
    {{ field }}
  {% endif %}
{% endmacro %}
```

